  "body": "# Problem\nSometimes, I just want to use a dapp or send / receive assets. I don't care about chat at that moment - maybe I'm on a limited connection, maybe others in my household are using the internet for streaming and fetching messages would kill this, maybe I literally don't need chat, I just want to send some eth. Status starts syncing chat by default, which is detrimental to UX in such use cases.\n\n# How to solve\nIntroduce a \"start in:\" selector to options.\nOptions available:\n\n* wallet only mode\n* chat + wallet mode\n\nWhen Status is in wallet only mode, make chat refresh a manual process by either long-pressing on chats, or by toggling a settings switch, or something else.\n\nIn a nutshell, allow for a wallet-only mode of Status.\n\n- - -\nNote this would also disable chat under dapps. An acceptable compromise.\n\n",
